                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">““Do you not know that to whom you present yourselves slaves to obey, you are that one’s slaves whom you obey, whether of sin leading to death, or of obedience leading to righteousness? But God be thanked that though you were slaves of sin, yet you obeyed from the heart that form of doctrine to which you were delivered. And having been set free from sin, you became slaves of righteousness.”
                                                                            <b>Romans 6:16-18 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Yet indeed I also count all things loss for the excellence of the knowledge of Christ Jesus my Lord, for whom I have suffered the loss of all things, and count them as rubbish, that I may gain Christ and be found in Him, not having my own righteousness, which is from the law, but that which is through faith in Christ, the righteousness which is from God by faith;”
                                                                            <b>Philippians 3:8-9 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">As we assemble the pieces of the full armor of God in position let us realize that each piece is strategically positioned, each piece equally important yet having different functions.  As stated the Belt of Truth is foundational, it covers the lower abdomen and ties down the outer tunic of the soldier that he may move freely.  The Breastplate of Righteousness could be considered the key.  Without righteousness, being in right standing with God we have no access to the armor. No access to even the foundation which is the Belt of Truth , nor any other piece of the armor of God.  If we are not in Christ we are not covered in righteousness.  We are yet slaves to sin.  But God be thanked that though we were slaves of sin, yet we obeyed from the heart that form of doctrine to which you were delivered.  (The Word of God) And having been set free from sin, we became slaves of righteousness.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">This is not a righteousness of ourselves as Paul says in Philippians the righteousness through faith in Christ.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Let us be reminded of the two men praying in <b>Luke 18:9</b>  Two men went up to the temple to pray, one a Pharisee and the other a tax collector. The Pharisee stood and prayed thus with himself,  God, I thank You that I am not like other men—extortioners, unjust, adulterers, or even as this tax collector. I fast twice a week; I give tithes of all that I possess.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">And the tax collector, standing afar off, would not so much as raise his eyes to heaven, but beat his breast, saying,  God, be merciful to me a sinner! I tell you, this man went down to his house justified rather than the other...
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Justified means made righteous.  If we for one moment think we have it together as this first man did, this is self-righteousness.  There is no breastplate made of self righteousness.  One will not be able to stand against the enemy.  We position ourselves with an attitude of humility as the second man did, we are sinners saved by grace, covered with the blood of Jesus, walking out our salvation with fear and trembling.  We will never fully arrive until that great day we step into eternity.  God’s instruction to us is to awake to righteousness and not to sin...<b>1Corinthians 15:34</b>. The context to this verse is to not forsake learning the word of God and applying it to our lives.  Let this refer us back to the Belt of Truth!
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">If we are wearing the Belt of Truth then we are learning, applying and walking out the word.  Our commitment to Christ will be evident, and flow from a heart of love.  His righteousness within us will make visible the Breastplate of Righteousness to His glory and therefore our stance in this daily battle will be sure footed.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Lord we bow humbly as the tax collector even knowing we have Christ, because Your word tells us there is not one that is righteous.  Our prayer today is to continue to be a slave to righteousness and live our lives in such a way the door to sin can’t be opened.  That we not allow the enemy access to any area of our lives. Your word also tells us in times of assault to draw near to You and the enemy will flee.  We thank You Father as all has been provided for us to come to know You, receive Your Son, eternity, life here more abundantly...You have done it all for us...may we glorify You...In Jesus Name!
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">If you are feeling you have not made a commitment to Christ and recognize that in fact you have been a slave to sin and would like to speak and pray with someone please fill this form.
